# Cloudflare Pages _redirects. Copied verbatim from `frontend/public/` into
# `dist/` at build time by Vite's static-asset pass. First match wins.
#
# 404.html turns off SPA fallback for unmatched paths — see ADR-0004
#
# Trailing-slash → non-trailing canonical. The build emits `dist/<slug>.html`
# (file, not directory) for every indexable route, so Pages serves `/<slug>`
# with 200 directly. Anyone who lands on `/<slug>/` — old inbound links,
# third-party share tools that auto-append `/` — gets a 308 to the canonical
# no-trailing form. Search Console previously flagged the (old) `/<slug>` →
# `/<slug>/` 308 chain as "page avec redirection", suppressing the indexable URL.
#
# 308 (not 301) preserves the request method on rewrite; matches the
# default Cloudflare Pages emits for the inverse rule.

/grille/             /grille             308
/grilles/            /grilles            308
/aide/               /aide               308
/mentions-legales/   /mentions-legales   308
/confidentialite/    /confidentialite    308
/privacy/            /privacy            308
/compte/             /compte             308

# /sondage → /contribuer: server-side 308s because SPA fallback is gone (ADR-0004)
/sondage/pairs/      /contribuer/pairs   308
/sondage/pairs       /contribuer/pairs   308
/sondage/            /contribuer         308
/sondage             /contribuer         308

# lobby/join: 200 rewrite (no prerendered file) — client resolves param (ADR-0026)
/lobby/*             /                   200
/join/*              /                   200
